description:
Fone Bone and Smiley sneak out of the compound to release the Rat Creature cub, but Smiley strays out of sight with the cub,and Fone goes after him. Thorn tries to return home to the farm house, but collapses with exhaustion on the way, where four Veni Yan monks catch up with her and return her sword, which she left at the Barrelhaven. In her dream, she meets the Great Red Dragon, who convinces her not to run away by showing her visions of her friends, her grandmother, and Rat Creatures coming to attack them.

The next morning, Phoney Bone puts his “dragonslaying” plan into action, rallying the townsfolk to carry him and his cache of loot into the mountains where, he tells them, he will capture and kill a dragon.
name: The Turning

description: Brainiape, who is revealed to be Adolph Hiter's brain preserved within the body of a gorilla, is sent on a mission to kill the Dragon by Cyberface, the defacto leader of the Vicious Circle. Cyberface is decomposing, so to save him, Abner Cadaver summons the creatures of the undead, who attack the world-renowned paranormal investigator Hellboy.

Major Forsberg, a military strategist, has been kidnapped and imprisoned by Jason Wynn, a key figure in U.S. foreign intelligence. Forsberg had determined the insights of the great conqueror Genghis Kahn and relayed some of this to Wynn. When Forsberg denied having full knowledge, his family is murdered by Wynn. Forsberg believes that Wynn is inhabited by Kahn's spirit. Spawn frees Forsberg from Wynn's prison. Meanwhile, Clown continues to direct Wynn to destroy Spawn and Cy-Gor awaits Spawn's return to Rat City.
name: Kahn
Front Page: A Daily Bugle Report

description:
Elektra vs. Bullseye — Round Two! It's the rematch of the century as the beautiful assassin comes face-to-face with her nemesis, the cold-blooded killer known as Bullseye! He murdered her once; can he do it again?! This match ends in someone's sudden death!

Elektra engages in a good old fashioned grudge match against the man who killed her: Bullseye.
name: Father's Day

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Note: While Norman Osborn has a speaking role, his face is kept hidden throughout the issue.
name: Revelations, Part 2 of 4: Deadly Diversions

description: Peter and Mary Jane seek closure from their terrible loss. Meanwhile, Dr Kafka ponders on how to cure Chameleon.
name: A New Day Dawning

description:
Matt Decker is forced to join Omega Squadron and he is not happy about being in the same squad as cadet Nog the Ferengi.  Matt is an upstanding guy but cannot see a Ferengi in Starfleet.  Nog on the other hands can't seem to help but prove Decker is right.  The rest of the crew are also learning to deal with each other except Kamilah Goldstein and T'Priell who are already friends.
 
Everything comes to a head on a holosuite mission that goes wrong.  A new alien life form has taken control and could kill the whole squad and sends everything after them even a new and souped up group of Gorn Warriors..  Fortunately, they are able to work together and maybe even build friendships with even the likes of Nog.
name: Prime Directives

description: Continuing an all-new three-part thriller! When Neelix and Chakotay go to the rescue of a vanished Talaxian ship, they find themselves trapped -- and cut off from Voyager -- in a dimension of crystal towers and ephemeral beings!
name: Under Ion Skies

description: Josh Guthrie brother of sam(Cannonball) and Paige(Husk) finds a sentinel that follows his every order. He tries to be a hero using the robot but he just makes things worse. When his brother and sister come home to visit they try to take care of the sentinel once and for all. The sentinel defeats them both and when it was about to kill them, Josh stepped in the way and convinced it to destroy itself to protect him.
name: What if Cannonball's little brother kept his pet sentinel?

description: The inner circle (Hellfire Club) reunite to fight against Bastion.
name: Falling Up

description: Five X-Men (Cyclops, Phoenix, Rogue, Bishop, and the Beast) and Binary are on Starcore research station helping out when Binary attacks them!
name: Fugitive From Space/Junction

description:
The massive ship hovers over the team and Alia Rellapor delivers a warning when Spukler meets up with an old business partner. 
 
The Great wall of Thrudd lives up to its name and gives the team pause for thought.

name: I Have The Strangest Feeling I've Been Turned Into A Puppet!

description:
The X-Men must stop Havok and his Brotherhood from killing J. Jonah Jameson!

Spider-Man (Ben Reilly), at first mistaken for an intruder by Bishop, advises the X-Men that the Daily Bugle is investigating Graydon Creed. Later, at X-Factor's headquarters, Mystique plots Creed's death and discovers Bobby Drake has infiltrated Creed's campaign. At the same time, J. Jonah Jameson takes a flight to London to meet with Nick Bandouveris, a reporter who has learned the truth of Creed's background and now fears for his life. Jameson tells Beast, who is the same flight, he is aware the X-Man is there to tail him, while elsewhere on the SST, Scott Summers more successfully maintains his civilian guise. Storm and Joseph follow in the cloaked Blackbird.

Nearing England, the Concorde is attacked by Havok. Scott tackles Havok, disabling the latter's anti-gravity unit, and the two plummet to the coast below. As they freefall, Havok tells Scott that, for the first time, he is doing as he wants, not acting under another's influence. As Joseph magnetically sees the SST safely to Heathrow, Havok teleports away, and Storm rescues Scott at the last moment.

In London, as Bandoveris awaits Jameson, the reporter is killed, and the Creed file taken, by Bastion.
name: Fight and Flight!

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description:
Aquaman goes to Japan to find Porm's murderer.

Aquaman, Koryak and Dolphin are following the dolphins as Porm's body is being taken for the highest burial available in dolphin culture.Aquaman then asks for Dolphin's aid in his search for justice for his mother's death deciding to set out after dealing with Triotnis, with Aquaman ordering the citizens of Poseidonis to rebuild the city and serve Iqula however he sees fit with Koryak remaining behind to assist for his part. Aquaman and Dolphin then travel to Japan meeting with the American councilman demanding to meet with the company called Raiden Industries, as there symbol was branded into his mother's side.

Aquaman then questions the company founder who denies involvement but is found to be lying when Demon Gate arrives revealing his systems allow him to find tagged dolphins. He then reveals he did it all to draw the king their for his vengeance . The two then begin a battle which leads them through the building, until Dolphin knocks him from it incapacitating him. However Aquaman is prevented from killing him by the police's arrival, and attempted arrest. Ultimately Aquaman seeks the government to turn him over, with them refusing spurring Aquaman to ban them from the oceans and deliver a notice of war with in 24 hours if he is not turned over. Aquaman then calls in a giant squid to destroy a ship to show the government he is serious.
name: The Rising Sun

description:
On a mission to rescue Copycat from the Psycho-Man, Cable, Domino and Garrison Kane enter the Microverse via the sub-space vessel Endeavor. They are attacked by Psycho-Man's drone ships, which are repelled by the Micronauts (Commander Rann, Mari and Bug) who have just beamed aboard. Despite an altercation between Kane and Bug, they agree to join forces. Meanwhile, in San Francisco, G. W. Bridge investigates the ruins of Kane and Copycat's home, but is called back to S.H.I.E.L.D. headquarters.

In the Microverse, with Copycat mimicking the form of Kane, Psycho-Man makes a futile attempt to extract the secret of Kane's bionic technology from her body, hoping to augment his Dog-Soldiers. Copycat reverts to herself, and Psycho-Man realizes he can use her as bait.

Nearby, Cable's group approaches Psycho-Man's lair and are attacked by Dog-Soldiers. Cable succumbs to Psycho-Man's mental attack, and as Kane breaches the fortress, he is subjected to the villain's hate beam, an emotion directed at Cable.
name: In Perspective

description: Jack Hawksmoor investigates a murder in New York City.

Action and honor used to make a hero . . . now that's the media's job. Tina's past comes back to haunt her when her best friend is murdered. The Black Pearl is a hero, not a psycho . . . isn't he? With Tina running for her very life, reporter Frank Moran's frantic search for The Pearl gains an almost unbearable urgency. Stung by his show's cancellation, shock jock Jerry Delman plots a pay-per-view comeback as the merchandising machine is pushed to dizzying heights! Be careful, Luther Drake. You'll soon learn why justice is hard! The madness mounts when the mask goes on . . . don't miss it!
Sanctuary attacks their rival guild only to run into the Blood Guard in the process.
name: Seven: Retribution

deck: Under the darkness of The Final Night, Gorilla Grodd has Supergirl under a magic spell, and Leesburg sinks further into madness. Supergirl must face the her inner demons to triumph.
description: Unofficial Final Night tie-in. Supergirl fights to break free of Gorilla Grodd's control in "Belly of the Beast." Part 2 of 2, continued from the previous issue.
name: Belly of the Beast

description: Dick began moving into his new apartment, then met up with Soames. He sent Nightwing to a check cashing place in the ghetto; it was held up while he was there. Dick once again stopped a False Facer's heist. Afterwards, he contacted the Batcave on his progress. Batman offered his assistance, but Nightwing assured him that he could take care of it.
name: The Freebooters

description:
It’s the strangest Legion team-up yet as the group turns to Deadman for help in rescuing Apparition before she dissipates completely.

Apparition encounters Deadman, who aids her in freeing Ultra Boy from a psychic entity.
name: She's Not There

description:
Two Marshville residents and their baby refused to take refuge with the others in the safety of the city. They are both killed one day by a dinosaur attack and their baby is left hidden to fend for itself. While nervously giving a speech about the upcoming rainy season and some general safety tips, Meriem hears a voice that tells her there is a baby in trouble. The voice isn't her Grandfather's but is instead a hermit named Roberto Armstrong. Otherwise known as "Mr. Voodoo". Meriem finds the baby while Bruce, Prof. Cook, Captain Lavery, and Sgt. Higgins follow in one of the Professor's exploratory vehicles.

Klyde is seen trashing the power plant which causes electricity problems.
name: Chapter One: Homecoming

description:
The storms are finally coming. Meriem has rescued the baby and is washing it near a waterfall. She's having a lot of fun with the child and really enjoys making it laugh. Her grandfather appears to her and tells her they re being hunted. With the baby secure in a backpack she plans to climb a high tree and knock the Bird Claws off. They are smart though and try to get ahead of her on adjacent trees. She manages to elude most of them and even punches one in the face. She makes it to the electric plant and finds body parts and Klyde's foot prints. He's still there. She uses sign language to tell him that lizards are coming to hurt little Gramp and that she is weak. He roars and surprises the Bird Claws when they show up.

Prof. Cook is driving his armored speedster along with passengers Cap. Lavery, Sgt. Higgins and Bruce Kabbit. On their way to the electrical plant they try to rescue a man who left the safety of the Compound (what the towns people are calling the mall) to retrieve his beloved truck. A T-Rex and Triceratops fight has broken out and the Professor is loving it. It looks as though the Triceratops is killed but just as the Rex is going to eat the man the Triceratops pierces it's torso with it's horns and kills it. They collect the man whose truck is now destroyed and continue to the power plant.

Lumpy and some guys are trying to get some comics to read. The owner of the shop agrees to give them each $40 in comics and promises to keep the kids' club a secret if they help him move them to the compound. They agree and move everything over. Lumpy sees a dinosaur attack a policeman and the owner orders everyone into the storage room. One of the dinosaurs crashes through the window and attacks him.
name: Chapter Two

description:
A dialogue free issue that takes place about half a year before Mereim's hometown of Marshville is sent to the past.

Meriem is asleep in a high tree dreaming of her Grandfather and her eating McDonalds. She wakes up in the talons of a large winged dinosaur. After getting the best of it and now riding it she gets flung off and falls through trees, down a cliff side and lands hard. A little weary but uninjured she notices giant spiders and bees coming at her so she dives into a nearby lake. A large dinosaur swallows her but she fights her way out and knocks it in the head.

She climbs the large cliff and listens to her stomach rumbling when she finally reaches the top. She eyes a tiny lizard and just as she is about to eat it she sees a pack of feasting dinosaurs (maybe Raptors). They charge her as she runs to a hole in a tree and jump above it. A large fist comes out of the hole and nails one of the dinosaurs. It's Klyde and he begins to fight them all by himself. It looks there are too many for him but Meriem thinks back to when he attacked her and she hesitates helping him. He kills them and she gets away. She finds an insect and right before she puts it in her mouth she thinks back to McDonalds and can't eat it. She looks up at the sky with tears in her eyes and the only words written in the story appear:

"The mightiest struggles are fought from within ourselves though the key to winning is simple...keep smiling"
name: Missing McDonalds

description:
The storms have begun and even the animals are scared. Professor Cook, Capt. Lavery, Sgt. Higgins and Bruce Kabbit are stuck in the mud. They're trying to get Prof. Cook's vehicle out when Meriem show up with the baby. She gives it to Bruce to hold and easily frees the thing from the mud. She tells them she was just at the electric plant and Klyde is the reason the power is out. They are radioed about cyclone activity and try to avoid one.

Sgt. Marstone rallies up some of the locals and makes them gun crazy. He supplies them with weapons and proposes a dinosaur hunt. All of the kids in the comic shop are safe in the storage room when they hear movement on the other side of the door. It turns out to be the owner and he's ok. There is one more dinosaur and he crashes through the door. The owner kills it. The twisters have frightened a herd of Triceratops and they stampede through the town. Corporal Mack stumbles in on Marstone's speech and she tries to talk him out of it citing several examples of why it's a bad idea. He ignores her.

Meriem and them, all crammed into the Professor's vehicle drive through the hole the Triceratops herd made. Meriem jumps out and wants to help. She saves a little girl and her injured father. Sgt. Marstone and crew rescue a group of people stuck on a balcony but almost kills them in the process. Capt. Lavery sees the whole thing and yells at him. He tells her you can't just take a Triceratops by the nose and lead it out of town. Back at the comic shop, Klyde crashes in and grabs Lumpy. Lumpy tries to sign to him that he's OK but Klyde takes him anyways.

Meriem is struggling with the stampeding Triceratops that is in front of the herd. She's steering it using it's horn. The herd rumbles right past Sgt. Marstone and Capt. Lavery. Bruce takes the opportunity to point out you CAN lead one out of town by the nose. Meriem sees Klyde with Lumpy a short while later and stands right in the way. Her Grandfather appears and tells her she's foolish and that she should find a way to trick him instead. Klyde grabs her by the head and she kicks him but he manages to fling her away. She knocks over a steel post and then uses it as a weapon smacking Klyde on the head. He's doesn't seem hurt and grabs her. Just as his teeth are about to dig into her torso we see her scream off panel.
name: Chapter Three

description:
This issue starts out right where the last left off. Meriem gets chomped by Klyde. She scratches at his eyes and he throws her to the ground. She's down and hurt and Klyde is coming. The kids from the comic shop are trying to warn her but she isn't moving. Lumpy throws himself over her to protect her. Klyde stops and tells him to move through sign language. Lumpy tells him that the big lizards will hurt Lumpy and Meriem can't stop them because she is weak. Klyde runs to stop them and Meriem gives Lumpy a kiss on the cheek for his bravery. She finds a dead dinosaur to eat to speed up her healing factor.

The comic shop owner and the kids scramble into a moving truck to escape some large carnivores. Meriem tries to slow them down and Klyde tackles them both. They speed away as Klyde is beating the dinosaurs. When he finishes with them he chases after the van. The kids are throwing out boxes of comics to try and lighten it up. Kirby's Fantastic Four gets reluctantly tossed. Meriem thinks she can slow Klyde down. A man dressed in a Star Trek uniform named Williams offers to help Capt. Lavery and Bruce. She agrees and him and Bruce discuss the "Curse of Roddenberry". The idea that an extra is brought in just for one scene to get killed for drama. The three of them hear a rumbling and see another twister headed their way. They take cover under a bridge. Under that bridge though is a gigantic snake. It strikes at Bruce but Williams pushes him out of the way and is grabbed. The snake coils and squeezes. Capt. Lavery shoots it and it lets go just as the twister arrives. The snake gets picked up and swept away. Williams dies.

The giant snake lands right in front of Sgt. Marstone and his hunting party. They find Meriem and Klyde fighting and Marstone shoots a grenade round injuring both Klyde and Meriem. Meriem is down but Klyde rushes and attacks the group. Gramp appears to Meriem and tells her she needs to stop Klyde for good. She knows and jumps on Klyde's back repeatedly stabbing him in the neck with her knife. Marstone is going to fire again but Professor Cook warns him not to or else he'll blast him with the flamethrower his armored speedster is equipped with. They both fire. Marstone's feet get burned and his shot goes high knocking a wall down on Meriem and Klyde. Marstone rushes over and punches Professor Cook in the face. Bruce see this and slugs Marstone in the face. It doesn't even hurt him and Bruce is pounded to the ground. Lavery stops him and Marstone offers her a free shot like Bruce got. She whacks him in the throat, then the groin and then kicks him in the face when he's down.

Meriem stirs from the rubble and Klyde springs out with her in his fist. e slams her to the ground. Lavery empties her gun into Klyde's back but it has no effect. He rushes her and Professor Cook yells for her to get out of the way. She does and Klyde slams into his car. The Professor hits a switch and Klyde is electrocuted. Klyde slumps to the ground after it's switched off. Bruce tries to get to Meriem as Professor Cook is trying to restart her heart but it's too late. She's gone.

Professor Cook and Bruce bury Meriem and Prof. Cook says a few kind words. Two weeks later the citizens of Marshville have taken shelter in the Marshville Museum of Science to wait for the rains to stop. Food is running low and the electricity is out. The only water they can get is coming from the storm drains. While waiting for a stew to be ready, some of the people gathered around tell stories of Meriem's various heroics. On the second floor of the Museum some men are performing an autopsy on Klyde. They are a little jumpy. Bruce tells the kids about how she survived that time she saved them (back in her original series). She told him she knew she'd be OK after she stopped breathing and Lumpy gets his hopes up that's she's alive even though it's been two weeks.

There is a rumbling and part of the building caves in sending Bruce and a girl he used to know into a sewer with large Crocodile like reptiles. Lumpy tells Prof. Cook that Bruce might believe it too and that he went to her grave to see. The Professor heads there right away to help Bruce. It's around this time that Klyde wakes up. He isn't dead and the men flee the room with Klyde behind them. Klyde stops and sees all of the people on the first floor from a balcony and they see him. Professor Cook arrives at her grave to see it overflowing with life. Plants and dinosaurs are surrounding it. He shoos them away and tries to fend the larger ones off with a club. He turns and sees Meriem standing behind him. He tries to say something but she tackles him. He says her name, confused, and she stabs him with a stake.

We learn the fate of Professor Cook. Meriem missed him with the stake from the previous issue. During the fight with Klyde her memory was damaged and she believes she is twelve years old again and doesn't remember anything past that. Doesn't remember Marshville coming back to the past and doesn't remember fighting with Klyde ever. Professor Cook tries to explain all this to her and she starts to believe him when he has her look at herself. Not the body of a twelve year old. She sort of remembers him and thinks they're in love. She runs off to find food before he can explain.

She appears to have reverted back to her feral self during those few years after Gramp died. She kills a dinosaur and that kill is taken by a larger one. She uses her skills to make a trap and catches and kills the meat thief. She observes Prof. Cook trying to radio Capt. Lavery who unbeknownst to him, is unconscious and quickly being surrounded by carnivores. She also watches him gather skunk spray (as seen in her Original Series) with out hurting the animal.

Klyde is scaring everyone in the museum so Lumpy tries to talk to Klyde with sign language. His friend Will goes with him. Lumpy tells Klyde that they are friends and it's ok but Klyde runs off. His memory isn't right either .

Bruce and the woman, Annette, are trying to dodge bites from giant crocodiles and stumble back into a little pit where the crocs can't get them. The little hole has dead bodies and beetles in it and Annette freaks out. One of the beetles burrows into Bruce's cheek. Annette makes the observation that the dead people weren't killed by the crocs because the bodies would be torn up. The beetles killed them. Bruce tells her not to worry about it because they're getting out. He eyes a storm drain.

More of the museum collapses and he anticipates a tidal wave. They make it to the grate and he swings her up. Before she can get him a crocodile takes a snap at him and barely misses. A huge eel is seem coiled around the crocodile. Bruce gets electrocuted by it. Electric eels. Annette lowers a belt down and pulls him up just as a tidal wave sweeps through the room. Once up through the grate he has her check his back and the end up both covered in beetles. Now they are stuck between that grate and another one higher up with the water level below them rising. They get to talking and Annette is the sister of the man who saved Bruce from the giant snake in Chapter 5. Bruce pulls out some booze and they make a toast to his memory.

name: Black Magic Part 1

description:
General Notes

Goldie has a single-panel appearance in The Dreaming as Skept's ghost-bird's hunt the spirit of Tamlin across all realms. Other realms briefly seen include Hell, Gemworld and Skartaris.
name: Dark As Day, My Lady, Bright As Night

description: A hypnotist from Bruce Wayne's past comes back looking for a amulet, and revenge on Bruce Wayne! Also starring Zantana/
name: Token of Faith

volume.name: The Batman and Robin Adventures Annual

name: Black Magic Part 2

description:
Pulp Heroes, this year's DC Annuals event, continues with three tales of hard-boiled undersea suspense. In the first story, a wife comes to Aquaman to help find her missing husband, Aquaman's old walrus friend Tusky, who they think has been either captured or killed.

Aquaman deals with an old friend who has gotten himself involved in various kinds of trouble.

In a secondary story, someone has infiltrated organized crime in Atlantis. But who is the rat? Who will live? Who will sleep with the ... um, never mind.
name: From Tusk 'til Dawn; The Lady in Cement; Wet City

description:
Overview

Classic Masked crimefighters from the 1940's are resurrected and reprinted in crystal clarity as part of AC's preservation of the history of comic books. Here's a thrilling adventure of Fox Feature's The Flame by the legendary Lou Fine, from Wonderworld #6, Fawcett Comics' Commando Yank "Takes A Vacation" from Whiz Comics #102, as drawn by Carl Pfeufer. Captain Flash, of Sterling Comics fame, faces "The Black Knight in a Mike Sekowsky-drawn story from Captain Flash #2, 1955; The Phantom Falcon appears in an unnamed Fiction House story, as drawn by Fermo, out of a 1949 issue if Wings,and you get another sexy tale of The Phantom Lady as she find that "Success Is No Accident", in a 1955 feature from her Ajax Comics run. As a special treat, Marvelman, the British version of Captain Marvel appears as he faces off with "The Pacifist". Originally published in England by L. Miller And Son im Marvelman #227, December, 1957. Golden Age history from two continents for less than seven bucks!! Color cover, interiors are black and white with graytones. 52-page standard comic book format.

Overview

MOM#5 A brand new painted cover by Dick Ayers and Bill Black leads off this issue,and The Black Terror is back in an exciting adventure by those champions of comic book noir, Jerry Robinson and Mort Meskin. This one is called "The Brute Of The Bayou", and it originally appeared in Nedor Comics' Black Terror #26, April of 1949. The luscious crimefighter Miss Masque (who was also revived in AC's Femforce title)makes her first appearance in this title, in "Death Stalks At Night",from America's Best Comics #27, August of 1948. It sports art by Bob Oksner, with some panels inked by a young Frank Frazetta! Captain Flash is back to defeat "The Actor", from Sterling's Captain Flash #2, 1955. M. E.'s The Avenger faces "The Red Hand Of Terror" by Dick Ayers, from The Avenger #1,in 1954; obcure Golden Age hero The Red Rocket also debuts this issue in "The Case Of The Wandering Evidence", from Ajax/Farrel's Phantom Lady #4. Plu, Mr. Mystic, by Bob Powell. This issue's "Story Behind The Cover", written by Bill Black, features illustrations specially created for it by Dick Ayers. Color painted cover, interiors are black and white with graytones. 52-page standard comic book format.
name: The Red Hand of Terror

description:
The next day Darrian wakes before Dawn after spending the night together and as she rises he sees her other eye for the first time. He tells her he has to be rid of the halo and will summon heaven and hell to him to make it happen. He tells her he knows he wont see her for a while when he leaves and Dawn confirms it.

Darrian stands in the shadow of the twin towers and clenches a raised fist. God and Lucifer appear before him, God demands the halos return making a slight at Lucifer as he does it. Darrian comments on how similar they look and recoils as they unite in rebuking him. Something Dawn once told him "Things only have the power that we give them" passes through his mind and without warning he smashes the halo. The two immortals seem satisfied with this and leave, the halo turned to gold.

Darrian pays for passage to Europa on a, converted to sail powered, aircraft carrier with the gold. He befriends the older captain with whom he has an instant connection. As they depart he sees the ruins of the cathedral through his bunks porthole.

Darrian dreams of Dawn asking him to break his fathers sword and wakes as he does so in a scene not unlike the smashing of the halo. He sits on the prow of the ship as it sails into a sunrise thinking of his father. In the sky a translucent Dawn rises from the horizon in a dramatic pose.
name: Strike While the Iron is

description: Pulp Heroes, the DCU Annuals event, continues with a tribute to the adventure magazines of the 1930s. Green Lantern is pulled into a mysterious painting where he find himself in a strange world with scenery that shifts from prehistoric jungles to underwater kingdoms. He uses his ring to create battle gear for himself and winds up unable to take it off! A beautiful woman asks him to help defeat the evil wizard of this world, which appears to be disappearing. Only one problem: If Kyle beats the villain, he'll be trapped in the painting forever.
name: Worlds Within Worlds

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight Annual

description:
An aspiring starlet is convinced that the Flash is the man of her dreams, and goes to any means necessary to make sure those dreams come true.

In this chapter of the "Pulp Heroes" Annuals we have a two part story. The first part deals with the Flash trying to make a movie so he can bring some income and give the profits to a small town. Unfortunately the rainbow Raider and a Femme Fatale bent on marrying the Flash put a damper on things.

The second story has the Pied Piper dealing with an old crime buddy who does not like that the Pied Piper gave up his life of crime.

Lucius Fox and his associate Karen Abrams are kidnapped in the hostile city Hasaguara to terrorists demanding a ransom from WayneCorp.

Batman goes alone to save him but unfortunately, gung ho Buzz Westlake of WayneCorp security disobeys Bruce Wayne's orders to pay the ransom and puts the mission in jeapordy.
name: Warrior Breed!

description: As the world wonders if Lex Luthor is truly the hero some believe he is, a former hero has turned colors! Maxima, former powerhouse of the Justice League, renews her vendetta against Superman by attacking Clark Kent and Lori Lemaris!
name: Maxima is Back!

description: The Wickedest Witch's powers continue to grow, along with the strength of the Goblin horde army, leading to a showdown with the Witch and the Goblin King. Lion, Jinjur and Jack Pumpkinhead discover the devastation wrought by the Quadlings upon the Lion's animal forest domain. And the Wizard and Amber Ombi butt heads over the role of the new All-Ozzian Army in this post-Nome King Oz. Based on the Wonderful Wizard of Oz books.
name: From Bad to Worse

volume.name: Tales Calculated to Drive you Mad

description: The Wickedest Witch consolidates her power as the new Queen of the Goblins. General Jinjur and Jack Pumpkinhead, on a mission to discover the source of the mysterious southern volcano, meet the Witch, with disastrous consequences. Meanwhile, Queen Ozma decides to embark on a diplomatic mission to Quadling Country to stop what may become a deadly Civil War in the land of Oz. Based on the Wonderful Wizard of Oz books.
name: The Season of the Witch

volume.name: Tales Calculated to Drive you Mad

description: "Clay" part 2. Desperate for more power, Matthew Hagen bathes in the mysterious clay pool to revitalize his fading abilities and goes mad! Nearly killed in their first battle, the Dark Knight must make a final attempt to stop Clayface or die trying.
name: Clay Part 2 of 2

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description:
Tommy attempts to escape from the Gotham City Police with a hostage in tow, but just when things seem to go his way, Mr. Truman and Feekle enlist some help to bring him in: Green Lantern Kyle Rayner! "Local Heroes" Part 2!

A police goon squad gather to take Tommy down. Dirty, rotten cops but nothing to kill them over. How can Tommy make it past a dozen well armed officers when he can't even fire a single bullet?
name: Local Hero Part, Two

description: The mysterious Lady in Red makes another appearance; Charity's sisters are arriving in Terminal City via zeppelin; and B.B. and Jezebel take a trip to Slantown to find out more about the contents of the strongbox.
name: Episode Seven

description: John Irons, the man called Steel, and his niece Natasha have relocated to Jersey City, where Steel takes the position of Head of Medical Research in a local hospital.
name: Bang

description: Cross is an ex-cop with a bad reputation fallen on hard times. While working his current gig, providing security for Chun Fat Lin's underground casino the place is hit by triad gangsters flying high on "firefly," a drug so hot addicts are prone to spontaneously combusting. Now the Mayor's campaign manager has turned up dead in the joint and Cross is finding himself wrapped up in something really dirty- politics.

Overview

Gather 'round as Barry Windsor-Smith: STORYTELLER continues tales from worlds long ago, far way, and yet to be. In Freebooters, the legend of Axus the Great's defeat of the monster Ammon-Gra is told as the wizard Uta-Prime plots revenge. In the lair of Willy the ape-man, The Paradoxman takes his first, brief trip on the Time Bike. And in Young Gods, Strangehands and Heros describe the traditional preparation of Dragon Tartar! Three tales, one vision -- the wit and artistry of Barry Windsor-Smith: STORYTELLER.

OverviewTarzan's battle with the evil Ahrtan is over, but the real danger has just begun! Tarzan and Mugambi are traveling through upper Kenya when they discover that an artifact of immense power has fallen into the hands of a Nazi private. It could make this lowly soldier the ruler of the world -- if he could only get out of the jungle! Thus begins "Tarzan and the Legion of Hate," the second story arc in the ongoing Tarzan series. This is a great place for new readers to swing into the action!
name: Legion of Hate (Part 1 of 4)

description: Politics and honor don't always mix. In a temple in which Usagi is staying with his friend, Priest Sanshobo, sanctuary is sought by a dying samurai who holds a secret that could change the course of the entire nation. Usagi and Sanshobo are bound to protect it, but there's a whole band of samurai determined to defeat them at any cost!
name: The Conspiracy Of Eight
Angel at War: The Fall of Saint Dumas - Part 2 of 3

story_arc_credits.name: Angel at War: The Fall of Saint Dumas

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: Angel at War: The Fall of Saint Dumas

description: Far north in the Arctic, Batman fights to save the tortured Man-Bat, who has now lost all humanity and is ready to destroy anyone and anything-including himself.
name: Darkest Night of the Man-Bat, Part 3: Predemption

description: A young criminal learns a sobering lesson when he's caught by Batman, but escapes with the aid of another felon. However, he finds himself forced to turn to the Dark Knight for help when the other crook tries to kill him!
name: Dagger's Tale

description:
The Storm of Chaos continues, now symbolized by two magical fish, Yin and Yang, battling each other.

Tim continues to float through the unending waters below the Tower of the Moon. He isn't drowning, but can't control his motion, and is tormented by the way the water spirits teased him about his fear of sleeping with Leah.

A six-armed shark-man, Aegaeon, suddenly comes by and hits Tim for being so accepting of his upcoming potential drowning. Tim knocks him back, magically.

The movie director, wielding his sword, is grabbed by a tentacle monster, but gets away. He continues looking for Mona, the actress, who is caring for Tim's body. He is angry at her for ruining the movie, as he sees it. He transforms into a tentacle monster himself, but also shrinks to miniature size.

Yin and Yang continue to cause tumult in the waters.

Leah doesn't want to drink the cup filled with the spirit of the mermaid. Her whole life has been about trying to escape a box and getting to be herself, and if she drinks, she'll once again be imprisoned and forced to live under another's ideas. But, to save Tim, she drinks it.

The shark-man, who embodies the idea of being a manly man, tells Tim to stop apologizing and accept his role as an Opener, and the use of force. He wants Tim to "grow a spine" and Tim responds by fighting back. The shark-man wants Tim to be more aggressive, and realizes Tim is afraid of himself. He doesn't know what to do with his power. Aegaeon agrees to train Tim.

Leah wakes up as a mermaid, and despite her former fears, loves her new reality. She sees the relationships between everything. She sees the Chaos Storm in a new way, and finds a bowl with the Yin and Yang goldfish. She feeds them, and they calm down.

Back in the real world, Mona and Tim sit alone, with the film crew all gone. Tim, taught by Aegaeon to understand how to accept responsibility for changing things, got rid of them by going back in time and changing the way the desert was protected by the law. Mona leaves, but Tim waits for Leah.

Tim is now more willing to do things, instead of just letting things happen. He is no longer afraid of his feelings for Leah.

Leah, however, is now stuck in her Tower, and can no longer even see Tim. They are separated.
name: Rites of Passage, Part Six: Drowning in Place

description: Part 2 of "Presidential Race" finds Flash running as fast as he can to keep his friend the Piper, who thinks the frontrunning Presidental Candidate is actually the resurrected villain the Top, from making the biggest mistake of his life.
name: Down to the Wire

description: Kyle Rayner gets together with John Stewart, Guy Gardner, and Alan Scott to toast to their fallen friend, Hal Jordan. Plus, Green Lantern faces his toughest challenge yet, babysitting Donna Troy's son.
name: Adventures in Babysitting

description: A series of sheep mutilations in Yorkshire prompt Chas to seek John Constantine's help--who accepts solely to escape the trail of an inquisitive reporter. But the answer to this mystery may actually lead to something far more sinister on the rise!
name: The Wild Hunt

description: The time-lost Legion of Super Heroes enlist Impulse's help to use the Cosmic Treadmill. The device, with a speeder running on it, is capable of time travel manipulation. After a few jumps in time, the Treadmill is seemingly destroyed. The Legion leave dejected. There is a flash of light; it turns out Impulse had sent the Treadmill itself a little bit into the future. Nobody realizes this.
name: A Little Knowledge

description: The Forever People and Lightray return as the pieces begin falling into place for Metron, who realizes what he and his fellow New Gods must do if they are to salvage anything of New Genesis and Apokolips!
name: The Gathering Storm
